Q.1 What is programming language ?
Ans. A programming language is a vocabulary and set of grammatical rules for instructing a computer or computing device to perform specific tasks.

Q.2 Why do we need a programming language?
Ans. A Programming language helps us to communicate with computer for performing given task.

Q.3 What are features of JAVA ?
Ans. JAVA  has following features
      1. Object Oriented
      2.Robust
      3. Platform Independent
      4.Simple
      5.High Level
      6.Multithreaded and Distributed
      
Q.4   What is an Object?
Ans. Object is a real world entity exist in environment.

Q.5  What is a class ?
Ans. Class is a logical template to create objects that share common properties and methods.

Q.6 Explain about the main() method in JAVA ?
Ans. The execution of the programme is start from main() method.
